{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# A simple single tone simulation\n",
    "\n",
    "- This simulation is very simple:\n",
    "   - The input consists of only one tone\n",
    "   - The embedding circuit is ignored (no harmonic balance)\n",
    "   - The DC I-V curve is generated through a polynomial model\n",
    "   \n",
    "- This simulation calculates:\n",
    "   - the pumped I-V curve\n",
    "   - the AC tunnelling currents\n",
    "   - the AC admittance\n",
    "   - the AC power delivered to the junction"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import qmix\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "%matplotlib notebook"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Define embedding circuit\n",
    "- Note: \n",
    "   - All of the circuit properties are normalized: \n",
    "      - voltages are normalized to the gap voltage (``vgap``), \n",
    "      - resistances to the normal resistance (``rn``), \n",
    "      - currents to the gap current (``igap = vgap / rn``), and \n",
    "      - frequencies to the gap frequency (``fgap``).\n",
    "   - This example doesn't include the embedding impedance, so you have to set the junction voltage (``vj``) manually"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# create an instance of the embedding circuit class\n",
    "# this holds all of the data about the embedding circuit (incl. voltage, impedances and frequencies)\n",
    "cct = qmix.circuit.EmbeddingCircuit()\n",
    "\n",
    "# set normalised frequency\n",
    "# (equivalent to the photon voltage (vph))\n",
    "cct.vph[1] = 0.33\n",
    "\n",
    "# set junction voltage (set drive level to alpha=1)\n",
    "vj = cct.initialize_vj()\n",
    "vj[1, 1, :] = cct.vph[1] * 1."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Generate response function\n",
    "\n",
    "- Here we will generate the response function using a polynomial model\n",
    "- This class will automatically generate the Kramers-Kronig transform of the DC I-V curve, and then setup the interpolation."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Generating response function:\n",
      " - Interpolating:\n",
      "    - DC I-V curve:\n",
      "       - npts for DC I-V: 273\n",
      "       - avg. error: 3.7010E-10\n",
      "       - max. error: 0.0000 at v=-1.10\n",
      "    - KK curve:\n",
      "       - npts for KK I-V: 330\n",
      "       - avg. error: 6.1923E-07\n",
      "       - max. error: 0.0001 at v=1.11\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "resp = qmix.respfn.RespFnPolynomial(p_order=50)\n",
    "\n",
    "resp.show_current();"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Calculate desired tunnelling currents\n",
    "\n",
    "- Note: \n",
    "    - ``qmix.qtcurrent.qtcurrent`` will calculate the quasiparticle tunnelling current based on the voltage across the junction ``vj``, the simulation parameters contained within ``cct``, and the response function ``resp``.\n",
    "    - The frequency that is solves for is the last argument passed to the junction below. For example, \n",
    "       - ``0`` corresponds to the DC quasiparticle tunnelling current\n",
    "       - ``cct.vph[1]`` corresponds to the AC quasiparticle tunnelling current of the first tone and first harmonic\n",
    "    - Normally, this is done by passing a list of frequencies that we want to solve for. Here, we select the first current in the list by adding ``[0]`` to the end of the function call"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Calculating tunneling current...\n",
      " - 1 tone(s)\n",
      " - 1 harmonic(s)\n",
      "Done.\n",
      "Time: 0.0046 s\n",
      "\n",
      "Calculating tunneling current...\n",
      " - 1 tone(s)\n",
      " - 1 harmonic(s)\n",
      "Done.\n",
      "Time: 0.0037 s\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "idc = qmix.qtcurrent.qtcurrent(vj, cct, resp, 0)[0].real\n",
    "iac = qmix.qtcurrent.qtcurrent(vj, cct, resp, cct.vph[1])[0]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Plot the pumped I-V curve"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots()\n",
    "\n",
    "# vertical lines for photon steps\n",
    "for i in range(-10,10):\n",
    "    ax.axvline(1 - i * cct.vph[1], c='gray', ls='--', lw=0.5)\n",
    "# plot I-V data\n",
    "ax.plot(resp.voltage, resp.current, label='Unpumped')\n",
    "ax.plot(cct.vb, idc, 'r', label='Pumped')\n",
    "# label the steps\n",
    "for i, lbl in zip(range(3), ['1st', '2nd', '3rd']):\n",
    "    vtmp = 1 - (i + 0.5) * cct.vph[1]\n",
    "    itmp = np.interp(vtmp, cct.vb, idc)\n",
    "    ax.annotate(\"{}\\nstep\".format(lbl), \n",
    "                xy=(vtmp, itmp+0.15), \n",
    "                xytext=(vtmp, itmp+0.15),\n",
    "                va='center', ha='center', \n",
    "                fontsize=7)\n",
    "# hw/e label\n",
    "ax.text(1-cct.vph[1]/2, 1.1, r'$\\hbar\\omega/e$', fontsize=8, ha='center', va='bottom')\n",
    "ax.annotate(\"\", xy=(1-cct.vph[1], 1), xytext=(1, 1), \n",
    "    arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle=\"<->\", color='k'))\n",
    "# other labels\n",
    "ax.set(xlabel='Bias voltage / Vgap', xlim=[0,2])\n",
    "ax.set(ylabel='DC current / Igap', ylim=[0,2])\n",
    "ax.legend(frameon=True);\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Plot AC currents"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots()\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.plot(cct.vb, np.abs(iac), 'k--', label=r'Absolute')\n",
    "ax.plot(cct.vb, np.real(iac), 'b', label=r\"Real\")\n",
    "ax.plot(cct.vb, np.imag(iac), 'r', label=r\"Imaginary\")\n",
    "ax.set(xlabel='Bias voltage / Vgap', xlim=[0,2])\n",
    "ax.set(ylabel='AC current / Igap', ylim=[-1,1.2])\n",
    "ax.legend(frameon=False);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Plot AC admittance"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots()\n",
    "\n",
    "y = iac / vj[1, 1]\n",
    "ax.plot(cct.vb, np.abs(y), 'k--', label=r'Absolute')\n",
    "ax.plot(cct.vb, np.real(y), 'b', label=r'Real')\n",
    "ax.plot(cct.vb, np.imag(y), 'r', label=r'Imaginary')\n",
    "ax.set(xlabel='Bias voltage / Vgap', xlim=[0,2])\n",
    "ax.set(ylabel='AC admittance')\n",
    "ax.legend(frameon=False);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Plot AC power delivered to the junction"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots()\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.plot(cct.vb, 0.5 * np.real(vj[1, 1] * np.conj(iac)))\n",
    "ax.set(xlabel='Bias voltage / Vgap', xlim=[0,2])\n",
    "ax.set(ylabel='AC Power / Pgap', ylim=[0,0.15]);"
   ]
  }
 ],
